  "educator_bios": {
    "Andrej Karpathy": "Former Tesla AI director and OpenAI founding member. Known for building things from scratch — GPT, tokenizers, neural networks — in a way that makes the internals unmistakably clear.",
    "Lilian Weng": "Head of Safety Systems at OpenAI. Her blog posts are the gold standard for comprehensive technical surveys — rigorous, well-sourced, and consistently referenced across the ML community.",
    "Jay Alammar": "Creator of the Illustrated Transformer and other landmark visual explainers. His diagrams have introduced millions of practitioners to attention, BERT, and GPT internals.",
    "Yannic Kilcher": "ML researcher known for deep, paper-by-paper video breakdowns. Covers everything from foundational papers to the latest arXiv submissions with technical depth and honest critique.",
    "Chip Huyen": "Author of Designing Machine Learning Systems and MLOPS-focused educator. Bridges the gap between research and production AI engineering.",
    "3Blue1Brown": "Grant Sanderson creates the most visually precise mathematical intuitions in existence. His neural network and attention series are entry points for thousands of learners.",
    "Sebastian Raschka": "Professor and researcher specializing in deep learning and model efficiency. Known for clear, code-grounded explanations of complex concepts.",
    "Christopher Olah": "Pioneer of interpretability research at Anthropic. His essays on neural network internals (circuits, features, mechanistic interpretability) are foundational reading.",
    "Hugging Face": "The open-source ML platform that democratized NLP. Their course and documentation set the standard for practical, hands-on transformer education.",
    "Simon Willison": "Creator of Datasette and prolific blogger on LLM tooling. Leading voice on Model Context Protocol, practical LLM usage patterns, and building tools that extend AI capabilities.",
    "Anthropic": "AI safety company and creator of Claude. Their documentation on agentic coding, Claude Code, and tool use patterns sets the standard for practical agent development."
  }
